            "description": "This project was undertaken for the IDEE Lab at MUMC+ at the Human Movement Lab. The aim of the project was to determine a novel method to classify different levels of physical activity such as sedentary, standing and dynamic activity. The research focused on using various data analysis techniques to extract features from raw acceleration signals of a triaxial accelerometer that could be used to classify the activity of a patient into different activity levels. ",
